## Delete Behavior Reference

| Table | Foreign Key | Delete Action | Effect |
|-------|-------------|---------------|---------|
| staff_accounts | staff_id | CASCADE | Delete staff → delete account |
| staff_accounts | department_id | SET NULL | Delete dept → set to NULL |
| departments | department_head_id | RESTRICT | Cannot delete if dept head |
| clients | account_manager_id | RESTRICT | Cannot delete if managing clients |
| projects | client_id | RESTRICT | Cannot delete client with projects |
| timesheets | staff_id | CASCADE | Delete staff → delete timesheets |
| timesheets | department_id | RESTRICT | Cannot delete dept with timesheets |
| timesheets | client_id | RESTRICT | Cannot delete client with timesheets |
| timesheets | project_id | RESTRICT | Cannot delete project with timesheets |

**Key Principles:**
- **CASCADE**: Use when child records should be deleted automatically
- **RESTRICT**: Use when you want to prevent accidental data loss
- **SET NULL**: Use when relationship is optional and you want to preserve the record

